info.title: OpenAPI Definition
info.description: The OpenAPI Specification is a standard format to define the structure and syntax of REST APIs. OpenAPI documents are both machine and human-readable, which enables anyone to easily determine how each API works. [More details](https://www.openapis.org/faq)

post.description: Approves a certificate for a connector/destination, so Fivetran trusts this certificate for a source/destination database. The connector/destination setup tests will fail if a non-approved certificate is provided.

Creates a new destination within a specified group in your Fivetran account. IMPORTANT: Groups and destinations are mapped 1:1 to each other. We do this mapping using the group's `id` value that we automatically generate when you create a group, and the destination's `group_id` value that you specify when you create a destination. This means that you must create a group in your Fivetran account before you can create a destination in it.

post.description: Triggers a full historical sync of a connector or multiple schema tables within a connector. If the connector is paused, the table sync will be scheduled to be performed when the connector is re-enabled. If there is a data sync already in progress, we will try to complete it. If it fails, the request will be declined and the HTTP 409 Conflict error will be returned.

update_state.description:
The current data update state of the connector. The available values are:
- on_schedule - the sync is running smoothly, no delays
- delayed - the data is delayed for a longer time than expected for the update.

setup_state.description:
The current setup state of the connector. The available values are:
- incomplete - the setup config is incomplete, the setup tests never succeeded
- connected - the connector is properly set up
- broken - the connector setup config is broken.

sync_state.description:
The current sync state of the connector. The available values are:
- scheduled - the sync is waiting to be run
- syncing - the sync is currently running
- paused - the sync is currently paused
- rescheduled - the sync is waiting until more API calls are available in the source service.

is_historical_sync.description: The boolean specifying whether the connector should be triggered to re-sync all historical data. If you set this parameter to TRUE, the next scheduled sync will be historical. If the value is FALSE or not specified, the connector will not re-sync historical data. NOTE: When the value is TRUE, only the next scheduled sync will be historical, all subsequent ones will be incremental. This parameter is set to FALSE once the historical sync is completed.

rescheduled_for.description: The scheduled time for the next sync when sync_state is rescheduled. If schedule_type is manual, then the connector expects triggering the event at the designated time through the [Sync Connector Data](https://fivetran.com/docs/rest-api/connectors#syncconnectordata) endpoint.

ALLOW_COLUMNS - all new schemas and tables which appear in the source after the initial setup are excluded from syncs, but new columns are included

The method to detect new or changed rows.
Supported values:
`BINLOG` - Fivetran uses your binary logs (also called binlogs) to request only the data that has changed since our last sync. This is the default value if no value is specified.
`TELEPORT` - Fivetran's proprietary replication method that uses compressed snapshots to detect and apply changes.

Otherwise, `Directly` is used as a value if the parameter is omitted.

update_method.description:
The method to detect new or changed rows.
Specify only for `"service": "postgres"` or `"service": "postgres_rds"`.
Supported values:
`WAL` - this method replicates new, changed and deleted rows by tailing the write-ahead log (WAL) via a logical slot. This is more efficient than the XMIN method, but requires more setup and monitoring.
`XMIN` - this method detects new or changed rows via the XMIN system column, but is not capable of detecting deleted rows.
`WAL_PGOUTPUT` - logical replication of the WAL using the pgoutput plugin. This method replicates new, changed, and deleted rows by tailing the write-ahead log (WAL) using a logical slot.
`TELEPORT` - Fivetran's proprietary replication method that uses compressed snapshots to detect and apply changes.

append_file_option.description: If you know that the source completely over-writes the same file with new data, you can append the changes instead of upserting based on filename and line number.

prefix.description: All files and folders under this folder path will be searched for files to sync.

pattern.description: All files in your search path matching this regular expression will be synced.

escape_char.description: If your CSV generator follows non-standard rules for escaping quotation marks, you can set the escape character here.

json_delivery_mode.description: Control how your JSON data is delivered into your destination

skip_after.description: We will skip over the number of lines specified at the end so as to not introduce aberrant data into your destination.

line_separator.description: You can specify the custom line separator for your CSV files. The line separator is used in files to separate one row from the next.

skip_before.description: We will skip over the number of lines specified before syncing data.

empty_header.description: Optional. If your CSV generating software doesn't provide header line for the documents, Fivetran can generate the generic column names and sync data rows with them.

null_sequence.description: If your CSVs use a special value indicating null, you can specify it here.

is_single_table_mode.description: Allows the creation of connector using Merge Mode strategy.

delimiter.description: You can specify the delimiter that your CSVs use here. Fivetran generally tries to infer the delimiter, but in some cases this is impossible.

file_type.description: If your files are saved with improper extensions, you can force them to be synced as the selected filetype.
file_type.example: csv | log | json | jsonl | infer | tsv | avro | parquet | xml | spreadsheet | unstructured

on_error.description: If you know that your files contain some errors, you can choose to have poorly formatted lines skipped. We recommend leaving the value as fail unless you are certain that you have undesirable, malformed data.

compression.description: The compression format is used to let Fivetran know that even files without a compression extension should be decompressed using the selected compression format.
compression.example: bz2 | gz | gzip | zip | tar | tar_bz2 | tar_gz | uncompressed | infer

archive_pattern.description: Files inside of compressed archives with filenames matching this regular expression will be synced.

enable_distributed_connector_mode.description: Enable to allow the connector to join a cluster of connectors forming a Distributed Connector Cluster. This cluster allows parallel syncs from the same source to the same destination using multiple connectors.

sync_pack_mode.description:
The packing mode type. Supported values:
`STANDARD_UNPACKED_MODE`- Unpacks _one_ layer of nested fields and infers types.
`PACKED_MODE`- Delivers packed data as a single destination column value.
Learn more in our [Azure Cosmos DB Sync Pack Mode Options documentation](/docs/connectors/databases/cosmos#packmodeoptions).

data_access_method.description:
The source data access method. Supported values:
`ACCOUNT_KEY`- Data access method that uses account keys to authenticate to the source database. It comes in both read-write and read-only variants.
`RESOURCE_TOKEN`- Fine-grained permission model based on native Azure Cosmos DB users and permissions.
Learn more in our [Azure Cosmos DB Data Access Methods documentation](/docs/connectors/databases/cosmos#dataaccessmethods).

account_key.description: The read-only primary or secondary account key for the database account. Required for the `ACCOUNT_KEY` data access method.

distributed_connector_cluster_size.description: Specifies the total number of connectors in the Distributed Connector Cluster running in parallel.

token_authenticated_database.description: The database name. Required for the `RESOURCE_TOKEN` data access method.

resource_token.description: A token that provides access to a specific Azure Cosmos DB resource. Required for the `RESOURCE_TOKEN` data access method.

append_file_option.description: If you know that the source completely over-writes the same file with new data, you can append the changes instead of upserting based on filename and line number.

prefix.description: All files and folders under this folder path will be searched for files to sync.

pattern.description: All files in your search path matching this regular expression will be synced.

escape_char.description: If your CSV generator follows non-standard rules for escaping quotation marks, you can set the escape character here.

json_delivery_mode.description: Control how your JSON data is delivered into your destination

skip_after.description: We will skip over the number of lines specified at the end so as to not introduce aberrant data into your destination.

line_separator.description: You can specify the custom line separator for your CSV files. The line separator is used in files to separate one row from the next.

skip_before.description: We will skip over the number of lines specified before syncing data.

empty_header.description: Optional. If your CSV generating software doesn't provide header line for the documents, Fivetran can generate the generic column names and sync data rows with them.

null_sequence.description: If your CSVs use a special value indicating null, you can specify it here.

is_single_table_mode.description: Allows the creation of connector using Merge Mode strategy.

delimiter.description: You can specify the delimiter that your CSVs use here. Fivetran generally tries to infer the delimiter, but in some cases this is impossible.

file_type.description: If your files are saved with improper extensions, you can force them to be synced as the selected filetype.
file_type.example: csv | log | json | jsonl | infer | tsv | avro | parquet | xml | spreadsheet | unstructured

on_error.description: If you know that your files contain some errors, you can choose to have poorly formatted lines skipped. We recommend leaving the value as fail unless you are certain that you have undesirable, malformed data.

compression.description: The compression format is used to let Fivetran know that even files without a compression extension should be decompressed using the selected compression format.
compression.example: bz2 | gz | gzip | zip | tar | tar_bz2 | tar_gz | uncompressed | infer

archive_pattern.description: Files inside of compressed archives with filenames matching this regular expression will be synced.

prebuilt_report_name.description: The report name to which connector will sync the data. [Possible prebuilt_report values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads-insights/api-config#prebuiltreport).

view_attribution_window.description: Time period to attribute conversions based on views. [Possible view_attribution_window values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads-insights/api-config#viewattributionwindow).

breakdowns.description: List of breakdowns which connector will sync. [Possible breakdowns values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads-insights/api-config#breakdowns).

click_attribution_window.description: Time period to attribute conversions based on clicks. [Possible click_attribution_window values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads-insights/api-config#clickattributionwindow).

aggregation.description: Options to select aggregation duration. [Possible aggregation values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads-insights/api-config#aggregation).

table_name.description: The table name within the schema to which the connector will sync the data. It must be unique within the connector and must comply with [Fivetran's naming conventions](/docs/getting-started/core-concepts#namingconventions).

action_report_time.description: The report time of action stats. [Possible action_report time values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads-insights/api-config#actionreporttime).

engaged_view_attribution_window.description: Time period to attribute conversions based on engaged views. [Possible view_attribution_window values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads#engagedviewattributionwindow).

action_breakdowns.description: List of action_breakdowns which connector will sync. [Possible action_breakdowns values](/docs/connectors/applications/facebook-ads-insights/api-config#actionbreakdowns).
example: action_canvas_component_name | action_carousel_card_id | action_carousel_card_name | action_destination | action_device | action_link_click_destination | action_reaction | action_target_id | action_type | action_video_sound | action_video_type

update_method.description:
The method to detect new or changed rows.
Supported values:
`BINLOG` - Fivetran uses your binary logs (also called binlogs) to request only the data that has changed since our last sync. This is the default value if no value is specified.
`TELEPORT` - Fivetran's proprietary replication method that uses compressed snapshots to detect and apply changes.

update_method.description:
The method to detect new or changed rows.
Specify only for `"service": "postgres"` or `"service": "postgres_rds"`.
Supported values:
`WAL` - this method replicates new, changed and deleted rows by tailing the write-ahead log (WAL) via a logical slot. This is more efficient than the XMIN method, but requires more setup and monitoring.
`XMIN` - this method detects new or changed rows via the XMIN system column, but is not capable of detecting deleted rows.
`WAL_PGOUTPUT` - logical replication of the WAL using the pgoutput plugin. This method replicates new, changed, and deleted rows by tailing the write-ahead log (WAL) using a logical slot.
`TELEPORT` - Fivetran's proprietary replication method that uses compressed snapshots to detect and apply changes.

delimiter.description: You can specify the delimiter that your CSVs use here. Fivetran generally tries to infer the delimiter, but in some cases this is impossible.

file_type.description: If your files are saved with improper extensions, you can force them to be synced as the selected filetype.

on_error.description: If you know that your files contain some errors, you can choose to have poorly formatted lines skipped. We recommend leaving the value as fail unless you are certain that you have undesirable, malformed data.

compression.description: The compression format is used to let Fivetran know that even files without a compression extension should be decompressed using the selected compression format.

`WAL_PGOUTPUT` - logical replication of the WAL using the pgoutput plugin. This method replicates new, changed, and deleted rows by tailing the write-ahead log (WAL) using a logical slot.
`TELEPORT` - Fivetran's proprietary replication method that uses compressed snapshots to detect and apply changes.

`TELEPORT` - Fivetran's proprietary replication method that uses compressed snapshots to detect and apply changes.

`WAL` - this method replicates new, changed and deleted rows by tailing the write-ahead log (WAL) via a logical slot. This is more efficient than the XMIN method, but requires more setup and monitoring.
`XMIN` - this method detects new or changed rows via the XMIN system column, but is not capable of detecting deleted rows.
`WAL_PGOUTPUT` - logical replication of the WAL using the pgoutput plugin. This method replicates new, changed, and deleted rows by tailing the write-ahead log (WAL) using a logical slot.
`TELEPORT` - Fivetran's proprietary replication method that uses compressed snapshots to detect and apply changes.

empty_header.description: Optional. If your CSV generating software doesn't provide header line for the documents, Fivetran can generate the generic column names and sync data rows with them.

null_sequence.description: If your CSVs use a special value indicating null, you can specify it here.

is_single_table_mode.description: Allows the creation of connector using Merge Mode strategy.

share_url.description: Your SharePoint folder URL. You can find the folder URL by following the steps mentioned [here](/docs/connectors/files/share-point/setup-guide).

delimiter.description: You can specify the delimiter that your CSVs use here. Fivetran generally tries to infer the delimiter, but in some cases this is impossible.

file_type.description: If your files are saved with improper extensions, you can force them to be synced as the selected file type.
file_type.example: csv | log | json | jsonl | infer | tsv | avro | parquet | xml | spreadsheet | unstructured

on_error.description: If you know that your files contain some errors, you can choose to have poorly formatted lines skipped. We recommend leaving the value as fail unless you are certain that you have undesirable, malformed data.

compression.description: The compression format is used to let Fivetran know that even files without a compression extension should be decompressed using the selected compression format.
compression.example: bz2 | gz | gzip | zip | tar | tar_bz2 | tar_gz | uncompressed | infer

archive_pattern.description: Files inside of compressed archives with filenames matching this regular expression will be synced.

prefix.description: All files and folders under this folder path will be searched for files to sync.

pattern.description: All files in your search path matching this regular expression will be synced.

json_delivery_mode.description: Specifies how Fivetran should handle your JSON data. Default value: `Packed`.

skip_after.description: We will skip over the number of lines specified at the end to avoid introducing aberrant data into your destination.

empty_header.description: If your CSVs are headerless, set this is as `true`. When `true`, we will generate generic column names following the convention of `column_0`, `column_1`, ... `column_n` to map the rows. Default value: `false`.

use_pgp_encryption_options.description: Set to `true` if files are encrypted using PGP in the Wasabi Cloud Storage bucket. Default value: `false`.

skip_before.description: We will skip over the number of lines specified before syncing data.

signer_public_key.description: The contents of the signer's public key file. Must be populated if `use_pgp_encryption_options` is set to `true` and PGP encrypted files are signed.

delimiter.description: You can specify the delimiter that your CSVs use here. Fivetran generally tries to infer the delimiter, but in some cases this is impossible.

file_type.description: If your files are saved with improper extensions, you can force them to be synced as the selected file type.
file_type.example: csv | log | json | jsonl | infer | tsv | avro | parquet | xml | spreadsheet | unstructured

on_error.description: If you know that your files contain some errors, you can choose to have poorly formatted lines skipped. We recommend leaving the value as `fail` unless you are certain that you have undesirable, malformed data.

table.title: Destination table
table.description: Destination table. Table is permanent and cannot be changed after connection creation

archive_pattern.description: Files inside compressed archives with filenames matching this regular expression will be synced.

pgp_secret_key.description: The contents of your PGP secret key file. Must be populated if `use_pgp_encryption_options` is set to `true`.

auth_type.description: The Wasabi Cloud Storage Access approach. Required for connector creation. Default value: `ACCESS_KEY`.

append_file_option.description: If you know that the source completely over-writes the same file with new data, you can append the changes instead of upserting based on filename and line number.

escape_char.description: If your CSV generator follows non-standard rules for escaping quotation marks, you can set the escape character here.

bucket.description: The Wasabi Cloud Storage bucket name. Required for connector creation.

line_separator.description: You can specify the custom line separator for your CSV files. The line separator is used in files to separate one row from the next.

null_sequence.description: If your CSVs use a special value indicating null, you can specify it here.

region.description: The Wasabi Cloud Storage bucket region. Required for connector creation. Default value: `US_EAST_1`.
region.example: US_EAST_1 | US_EAST_2 | US_CENTRAL_1 | US_WEST_1 | CA_CENTRAL_1 | EU_CENTRAL_1 | EU_CENTRAL_2 | EU_WEST_1 | EU_WEST_2 | AP_NORTHEAST_1 | AP_NORTHEAST_2 | AP_SOUTHEAST_1 | AP_SOUTHEAST_2

compression.description: The compression format is used to let Fivetran know that even files without a compression extension should be decompressed using the selected compression format.
compression.example: bz2 | gz | gzip | zip | tar | tar_bz2 | tar_gz | uncompressed | infer

pgp_pass_phrase.description: The PGP passphrase used to create the key. Must be populated if `use_pgp_encryption_options` is set to `true`.
